      "comment": "MASTER MCGRAW (1) hit the ground running from an outside draw with a fast early split, paving the way for a 5.5 lengths win at Gunnedah over 527m in 30.14. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Looks to have an edge on most of these. ALL I SEE (2) goes very well at this journey having never missed the frame including four wins and two placings. Recorded a 0.8 lengths win (29.66) in a Grade 5 last time at Sandown. Can feature in the finish. STILTON SHINE (8) is an honest type in the frame at seven of 21 starts including last time when second (29.94) over 520m at this track. Goes well from this draw. Has a good overall strike-rate and can find the frame here. FEARLESS BANDIT (4) missed out after being heavily supported last time but should feature.",
